AT-0001.2: ##################################################################################
AT-0001.2: ########## GPSSpoofGradualLoiter (
        Full end-to-end spoofing experiment:

        Phase 1 - Nominal flight (arm, takeoff, fly to waypoint).
        Phase 2 - Inject gradual GPS velocity drift via SIM_GPS1_VERR (Feature 1)
                  and simultaneous position glitch ramp via SIM_GPS1_GLTCH (Feature 4).
        Phase 3 - Verify SUSPICIOUS notification arrives within 15 s.
        Phase 4 - Sustain attack; verify CONFIRMED notification within 60 s.
        Phase 5 - Remove spoofing; verify system lands cleanly.

        Spoofing model used:
          - SIM_GPS1_VERR_{X,Y}: linear ramp of velocity error in NED (m/s).
            This creates a persistent v_GPS - v_EKF residual that drives the
            CUSUM accumulator in compute_feature_vel_divergence().
          - SIM_GPS1_GLTCH_{X,Y}: simultaneous position glitch (degrees).
            Causes hAcc/sAcc inconsistency that drives Feature 4.
        )  ##########
AT-0001.2: ##################################################################################
